{{Youmay|the government body of Alderaan|[[High Council (disambiguation)|other uses of the word]]}}
Traditionally regarded as one of the primary ruling bodies of the destroyed planet of [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]], the '''High Council''' was a bulwark of that world's famed democratic system, despite it possessing a constitutional monarchy. The [[High Court of Alderaan|Royal House]] of Alderaan held governing power directly over the High Council, led by the [[House of Organa/Legends|House of Organa]] in its twilight years, but the High Council itself was representative of all sentients then living on Alderaan. Alderaan's [[Vizier/Legends|vizier]] presumably also sat on the High Council.

The ruling heirs to the [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaanian]] throne were expected to immerse themselves in the subtle niceties of social justice and political rule during their lifetimes; the majority of them served terms both in the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] as their people's representative (although at times this post was held by others not from the royal house, such as [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Bail Antilles/Legends|Bail Antilles]]), as well as on the High Council.

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The script of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], as presented in the ''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]'' interactive database, described Leia Organa as a member of the "Alderaan Senate".<ref name="btm">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref>

